decision_conditions: Reason : 1 - 1.	The submissions fails to provide: 1) safe and accessible pedestrian access to the site, given that that rear pedestrian access is not provided with a pavement that is at least two metres wide; 2) safe vehicular access to the site with the basement car parking layout, given the car circulation arrangement and parking bays which do not have 6 metre clearance; 3) a full assessment of the transport impacts of the development, as details of the access and use of the 138 parking spaces to the rear that share the same vehicular access to the proposed car parking spaces has not been provided; 4) an appropriate quantum and arrangement of cycle parking spaces for the quantum of residential units proposed for both short and long-stay cycle parking facilities and would therefore fail to encourage sustainable modes of transportation. The proposal would therefore be contrary to the terms of Paragraph MA.2.(2)(a) of Schedule 2, Part 3, Class MA of the General Permitted Development (England) Order 2015 (as amended).
